hope he is not ilL" 

Bernard sat listening, with his eyes on the ground. 

" Oh no, he is simply at home writing letters." 

Mrs. Vivian was silent a moment 

" I suppose he has a very large correspondence." 

" I really don't know. Just now that I am with 
him he has a smaller one than usual" 

" Ah yes. When you are separated I suppose you 
write volumes to each other. But he must have a 
