nervous, and don't know what I say. I am supposed 
to be agitated by Mr. Wright's departure ; is n't that 
it, mamma ? " 

Mrs. Vivian turned away, with a certain soft 
severity. 



 115 

" I don't know, my daughter. I don't understand 
you." 

A charming pink flush had come into Angela's 
cheek and a noticeable light into her eye. She 
looked admirably handsome, and Bernard frankly 
