ment, which she appeared to find extremely attrac- 
tive, " I know what you are going to say and I deny it. 
I am not fanciful, or sophistical, or irrational, and I 
know perfectly what I am about. Men are so stupid ; 
it *s only women that have real discernment. Leave 
me alone, and I shall do something. Blanche is silly, 
yes, very silly ; but she is not so bad as her husband 
accused her of being, in those dreadful words which 
he wiU live to repent of. She is wise enough to care 
