husband to-day that we had asked her, and that -we 
hoped he had no objection. * None whatever ; but 
she won't come.' * On the contrary, she says she will' 
* She will pretend to, up to the last minute ; and then 
she will find a pretext for backing out.' ' Decidedly, 
you think very ill of her/ I said. ' She hates me,' he 
